## Customer [/v1/customers/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (required, number) - Customer ID.

### List [GET /v1/customers{?size,from,sortBy}]

+ Parameters
    + size:   1           (optional, number)       - Page size.
    + from:   1           (optional, number)       - Start element (counting from 0) or # of elements to skip.
    + sortBy: `createdAt` (optional, enum[string]) - Field to sort by (`-fieldName` for descending order).
        + Members
            + `id`
			+ `isDisabled`
			+ `disabledBy`
			+ `isBlacklisted`
			+ `blacklistedBy`
			+ `blacklistedReason`
			+ `email`
			+ `name`
			+ `phoneNumber`
			+ `location`
			+ `modality`
			+ `isGuest`
            + `createdAt`
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomersList)

### View [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerResponse)

### Create [POST /v1/customers]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerCreatePayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerResponse)

### Update [PATCH]

+ Request (application/json)
	+ Attributes(CustomerUpdatePayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerResponse)

### Enable / Disable [POST /v1/customers/{id}/disable]

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (required, number)
+ Request (application/json)
	+ Attributes(CustomerToggleDisablePayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerResponse)

### Add To / Remove From Blacklist [POST /v1/customers/{id}/blacklist]

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (required, number)
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes(CustomerToggleBlacklistPayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerResponse) 

### Activate Guest [POST /v1/customers/{id}/activate]

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (required, number)
+ Request (application/json)
	+ Attributes(CustomerActivatePayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerResponse)

## Address [/v1/customers/{customerId}/addresses/{addressId}]

+ Parameters
    + customerId: 1 (required, number) - Customer ID.
    + addressId: 1 (required, number) - Address ID.

### List [GET /v1/customers/{customerId}/addresses{?size,from,sortBy}]

+ Parameters
    + customerId: 1       (required, number)       - Cusotomer unique ID.
    + size:   1           (optional, number)       - Page size.
    + from:   1           (optional, number)       - Start element (counting from 0) or # of elements to skip.
    + sortBy: `id` (optional, enum[string]) - Field to sort by (`-fieldName` for descending order).
        + Members
            + `id`
            + `regionId`
            + `name`
            + `address1`
            + `address2`
            + `city`
            + `zip`
            + `isDefaultShipping`
            + `phoneNumber`
            + `deletedAt`
            + `region_id`
            + `region_countryId`
            + `region_name`
            + `region_abbreviation`
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Addresses)

### View [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Address)

### Create [POST /v1/customers/{customerId}/addresses]

+ Parameters
    + customerId: 1 (required, number) - Customer ID.
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes(CreateAddressPayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Address)

### Update [PATCH /v1/customers/{customerId}/addresses/{addressId}]

+ Parameters
    + customerId: 1 (required, number) - Customer ID.
    + addressId: 1 (required, number) - Address ID.
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes(UpdateAddressPayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Address)

### Set as Default [POST /v1/customers/{customerId}/addresses/{addressId}/default]

+ Parameters
    + customerId: 1 (required, number) - Customer ID.
    + addressId: 1 (required, number) - Address ID.
+ Response 204 (application/json)

### Remove Default Address [DELETE /v1/customers/{customerId}/addresses/default]

This endpoint removes `isDefault` flag from any existing customer address.

+ Parameters
    + customerId: 1 (required, number) - Customer ID.
+ Response 204 (application/json)

### Delete [DELETE /v1/customers/{customerId}/addresses/{addressId}]

+ Parameters
    + customerId: 1 (required, number) - Customer ID.
    + addressId: 1 (required, number) - Address ID.
+ Response 204 (application/json)

